r-featuring-sad-models-without-bindi-internet-calls-it-funeral-collection-4549513%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RTI%20Appeal%20Body%20Remains%20Understaffed%20But%20Modi%20Government%20Names%20New%20Chair%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06133608%2Fsamariya.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20To%20prevent%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commission%20from%20becoming%20defunct%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20appointed%20Heeralal%20Samariya%20as%20the%20chief%20information%20commissioner%20(CIC).%20The%20post%20had%20been%20vacant%20since%20Yashvardhan%20Kumar%20Sinha%20retired%20on%20October%203%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20November%206%2C%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%20elevated%20Samariya%2C%20who%20has%20been%20an%20information%20commissioner%20since%20November%207%2C%202020%2C%20as%20the%20chief%20information%20commissioner.%20His%20term%20as%20information%20commissioner%20was%20set%20to%20expire%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20former%20secretary%20at%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Labour%20and%20Employment%20will%20now%20continue%20as%20the%20CIC%20until%20September%2013%2C%202025%2C%20one%20day%20before%20he%20turns%2065.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20terms%20of%20the%20two%20information%20commissioners%20%E2%80%93%20Saroj%20Punhani%20and%20Uday%20Mahurkar%20%E2%80%93%20will%20end%20today.%20On%20Monday%2C%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commission%20will%20have%20a%20strength%20of%20one%20CIC%20and%20two%20information%20commissioners%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20the%20full%20strength%20of%20a%20chief%20and%2010%20information%20commissioners.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fnew-chief-information-commissioner-2-commissioners-likely-to-be-appointed-today%2Farticleshow%2F104993244.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3EReports%20suggest%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Anandi%20Ramalingam%2C%20a%20former%20CMD%20of%20Bharat%20Electronics%20Limited%2C%20and%20V.K.%20Tiwari%2C%20a%201986%20batch%20Indian%20Forest%20Service%2C%20will%20also%20be%20sworn%20in%20as%20information%20commissioners%20by%20President%20Murmu%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20does%20not%20happen%2C%20there%20will%20not%20be%20any%20information%20commissioners%20in%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commissioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2030%2C%20hearing%20a%20petition%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20lamented%20that%20pending%20vacancies%20in%20information%20commissions%20could%20make%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act%20%E2%80%98a%20dead%20letter%E2%80%99.%20The%20apex%20court%20had%20asked%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20to%20fill%20up%20the%20posts%20of%20information%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20elevated%20Samariya%20to%20the%20post%20of%20CIC%2C%20it%20is%20yet%20to%20act%20on%20filling%20up%20the%20vacancy%20of%20eight%20information%20commissioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20three-judge%20SC%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20had%20also%20directed%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20to%20collate%20information%20from%20all%20states%20about%20the%20sanctioned%20posts%20of%20information%20commissioners%20in%20state%20information%20commissions%20(SICs)%2C%20how%20many%20such%20posts%20have%20been%20lying%20vacant%20and%20cases%20pending%20in%20each%20SIC.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20petitioner%20Anjali%20Bharadwaj%2C%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Frti-act-will-become-dead-letter-supreme-court-directs-states-union-to-fill-vacancies-in-information-commissions-241201%5C%22%3Eapprised%20the%20bench%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20despite%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%202019%20judgment%2C%20vacancies%20had%20not%20been%20filled%20up%20by%20the%20states%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20piling%20up%20of%20pending%20cases.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERTI%20activist%20Lokesh%20Batra%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcic-applications-no-new-appointments%5C%22%3Erevealed%20in%20August%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20not%20made%20any%20appointments%20in%20eight%20months%20to%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commission%20despite%20receiving%20256%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699258857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06133608%2Fsamariya.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fheeralal-samariya-appointed-as-new-chief-information-commissioner%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Heeralal%20Samariya%20was%20'elevated'%20as%20chief%20information%20commissioner.%20But%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20two%20other%20members%20of%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commission%20are%20set%20to%20expire%20on%20Monday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fheeralal-samariya-appointed-as-new-chief-information-commissioner%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nepal%20earthquake%3A%20Survivors%20cremate%20the%20dead%2C%20face%20uncertain%20future%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699257949000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F42A6%2Fproduction%2F_131626071_e406f39068e9fe0f05386518edfbbca92552a936-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67329796%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Homeless%20and%20sleeping%20in%20the%20cold%20outdoors%2C%20Nepal's%20earthquake%20survivors%20appeal%20for%20assistance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67329796%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67329796.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-67329796.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98The%20Difference%20Between%20Then%20and%20Now%E2%80%99%3A%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%20on%20Emergency%20and%20the%20Modi%20Years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06131557%2FScreenshot-2023-11-06-at-1.15.11%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ESeptember%2025%2C%201975.%20It%20was%20not%20the%20usual%20campus%20morning%20at%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20(JNU).%20A%20strike%20called%20by%20the%20Students%20Federation%20of%20India%20(SFI)%20to%20protest%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Ashoklata%20Jain%20%E2%80%94%20an%20elected%20councillor%20of%20the%20students%20union%20%E2%80%94%20was%20in%20its%20second%20day%20and%20the%20campus%20was%20tense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20three%20months%20since%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20declared%20a%20state%20of%20Emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20was%20on%20the%20lawns%20of%20the%20School%20of%20Languages%20that%20morning%2C%20with%20a%20few%20friends%20from%20the%20SFI%2C%20when%20a%20black%20Ambassador%20stopped%20near%20us%20and%20a%20burly%20man%20got%20out.%20He%20came%20up%20to%20me%20and%20asked%20if%20I%20was%20D.P.%20Tripathi%20%E2%80%94%20then%20president%20of%20the%20students%20union.%20I%20replied%20that%20I%20was%20not%2C%20but%20my%20questioner%20was%20a%20cop%2C%20DIG-Range%20P.S.%20Bhinder%2C%20and%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20believe%20me.%20He%20and%20his%20men%2C%20all%20in%20plainclothes%2C%20swiftly%20proceeded%20to%20kidnap%20me%20in%20broad%20daylight.%20I%20would%20end%20up%20in%20jail%2C%20kept%20there%20for%20a%20year%20under%20the%20Maintenance%20of%20Internal%20Security%20Act%20(MISA).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20370px)%2085vw%2C%20370px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22370%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front.jpg%20776w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front-194x300.jpg%20194w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06130239%2F20231011_prabir_purkayastha_good_fight_cover_front-662x1024.jpg%20662w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683676%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22572%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrabir%20Purkayastha%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EKeeping%20Up%20the%20Good%20Fight%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ELeftWord%20Books%20(October%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EFast%20forward%20by%20five%20decades.%20The%20government%20led%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20have%20been%20in%20power%20since%202014.%20They%20won%20a%20second%20term%20in%202019.%20The%20India%20we%20knew%2C%20that%20we%20thought%20of%20as%20home%2C%20was%20being%20changed%20by%20the%20day%2C%20in%20myriad%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFebruary%209%2C%202021.%20Morning%20again.%20I%20was%20at%20home.%20I%20had%20just%20finished%20breakfast%20and%20was%20reading%20the%20newspapers%20when%20the%20doorbell%20rang.%20It%20was%20a%20group%20of%20men%2C%20one%20of%20them%20with%20an%20official-looking%20paper%20in%20hand.%20They%20were%20from%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%2C%20he%20announced.%20The%20ED%20was%20here%20to%20conduct%20a%20raid.%20Their%20target%20was%20NewsClick%2C%20the%20digital%20web%20platform%20I%20had%20set%20up%20in%202009%2C%20and%20which%20had%20grown%20over%20the%20years%20in%20terms%20of%20both%20its%20work%20and%20its%20viewership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20raid%20continued%20through%20almost%20five%20days%20or%20113%20hours%2C%20and%20was%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20raids%20of%20a%20private%20residence.%20The%20record%2C%20as%20I%20would%20come%20to%20learn%2C%20is%20held%20by%20a%20raid%20lasting%20nearly%20ten%20days.%20It%20had%20taken%20place%20at%20the%20Jaigarh%20Fort%20of%20Rajmata%20Gayatri%20Devi%20%E2%80%94%20a%20place%20covering%20three%20square%20kilometres%2C%20somewhat%20larger%20than%20my%20second-floor%20flat.%20But%20no%2C%20the%20ED%20was%20not%20busy%20searching%20my%20flat%20all%20the%20time%20they%20were%20there%3B%20they%20could%20have%20easily%20finished%20within%20a%20few%20hours.%20Except%20that%20they%20had%20a%20%E2%80%98high-tech%E2%80%99%20problem%3A%20how%20were%20they%20to%20download%20my%20voluminous%20data%20from%20Google%3F%20Since%20Google%20throttles%20the%20speed%20of%20downloads%20beyond%20a%20certain%20limit%2C%20the%20downloading%20becomes%20excruciatingly%20slow%20after%20a%20few%20hours.%20My%20poor%20digital%20housekeeping%20had%20created%20a%20problem%20for%20the%20ED%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20for%20me.%20Hosting%20the%20ED%2C%20or%20any%20agency%20of%20the%20state%2C%20for%20almost%20five%20days%20is%20going%20beyond%20the%20call%20of%20hospitality%2C%20to%20put%20it%20mildly!%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMy%20earlier%20%E2%80%98emergency%20encounter%E2%80%99%20was%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20students%E2%80%99%20resistance%20in%20JNU.%20D.P.%20Tripathi%2C%20Ashoklata%20(usually%20called%20Ashoka)%2C%20Sitaram%20(Yechury)%20and%20others%20were%20among%20the%20key%20figures%20in%20that%20resistance.%20My%20encounter%20in%20the%20current%20%E2%80%98emergency%E2%80%99%20took%20place%20in%20rather%20different%20circumstances.%20NewsClick%2C%20a%20relatively%20small%20outfit%2C%20was%20somehow%20perceived%20to%20be%20a%20%E2%80%98problem%E2%80%99.%20Perhaps%20the%20problem%20was%20not%20so%20much%20NewsClick%20as%20the%20range%20of%20movements%20it%20covers.%20Just%20prior%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20unwelcome%20attention%2C%20NewsClick%20had%20covered%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement%20quite%20thoroughly%2C%20coverage%20that%20drew%20significant%20viewership%2C%20and%20not%20just%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20again%2C%20NewsClick%20was%20not%2C%20and%20is%20not%2C%20unique%20in%20its%20coverage.%20Many%20other%20digital%20platforms%2C%20and%20even%20certain%20mainstream%20media%2C%20have%20covered%20assaults%20on%20people%2C%20livelihood%20and%20reason%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20public%20protests%20that%20take%20place%20in%20response.%20Like%20us%2C%20some%20of%20these%20media%20organisations%20are%20very%20much%20under%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20scanner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20do%20not%20want%20to%20go%20into%20the%20various%20cases%20that%20NewsClick%20and%20I%20continue%20to%20face%3B%20or%20the%20campaign%20unleashed%20against%20us%20by%20a%20hounding%20variety%20of%20media.%20The%20legal%20matters%20are%20in%20the%20courts%20and%20we%20will%20fight%20the%20cases%20there.%20I%20have%20no%20desire%20to%20become%20the%20news.%20Nor%20does%20NewsClick%3B%20its%20job%20is%20to%20cover%20the%20news.%20It%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20what%20it%20has%20done%20from%20the%20time%20it%20was%20set%20up%3A%20follow%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20amplify%20the%20voices%20of%20those%20who%20are%20rarely%20heard%20in%20our%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20difference%20between%20then%20and%20now%20is%20at%20the%20fundamental%20level%20of%20ideology.%20The%20Congress%20ideology%20did%20not%20view%20certain%20sections%20of%20the%20people%20as%20outsiders%2C%20to%20be%20treated%20either%20as%20second-class%20citizens%20or%20excluded%20from%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%202014%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20dramatic%20increase%20in%20what%20we%20can%20only%20call%20hate%20crimes.%20Muslims%20have%20been%20the%20target%20in%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20these%20crimes%3B%20Dalits%2C%20Adivasis%20and%20women%20form%20part%20of%20the%20list%20as%20well%2C%20as%20do%20secular%20activists.%20Was%20it%20the%20same%20situation%20during%20the%20Emergency%3F%20Yes%2C%20there%20was%20oppression%3B%20but%20it%20was%20secular%20oppression.%20Yes%2C%20there%20was%20the%20Turkman%20Gate%20incident%20during%20the%20Emergency%2C%20when%20Muslims%20(and%20other%20residents%20of%20the%20area)%20were%20attacked.%20This%20incident%20illustrates%20a%20particular%20toxic%20combination%20of%20the%20Emergency%20agenda%3A%20family%20planning%20in%20the%20form%20of%20vasectomy%2C%20and%20demolition%20of%20poor%20areas%20to%20prettify%20the%20city.%20(Family%20planning%20expressed%20the%20fear%20of%20the%20middle%20classes%20that%20the%20poor%20were%20breeding%20too%20much%2C%20a%20favourite%20bugbear%20in%20the%20West%2C%20which%20saw%20the%20population%20growth%20of%20countries%20like%20India%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20their%20control%20over%20the%20globe%E2%80%99s%20resources.)%20But%20overall%2C%20the%20Emergency%20government%20was%20not%20trying%20to%20exclude%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIdeologically%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20not%20following%20the%20Savarkar%20thesis%20which%20plays%20out%20today%20both%20formally%20and%20informally%3A%20Minorities%20can%20remain%20in%20the%20country%20but%20only%20as%20second-class%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20not%20what%20the%20Congress%20ideology%20was.%20Nor%20what%20the%20national%20movement%20had%20built%3B%20certainly%2C%20the%20Congress%20could%20not%20publicly%20espouse%20such%20an%20ideology.%20The%20Congress%20could%20and%20did%20say%20that%20the%20Emergency%20was%20a%20necessary%20interim%20period%20of%20%E2%80%98discipline%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20Vinoba%20Bhave%20put%20it%2C%20%E2%80%98a%20festival%20of%20discipline%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Eapaatkal%20ka%20anushaasan%20parv%3C%2Fem%3E).%20The%20Emergency%20was%20described%20as%20a%20short-period%20fix%3B%20whether%20this%20was%20the%20only%20intent%20or%20not%2C%20it%20was%20not%20translated%20into%20a%20structure%20within%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20seeing%20something%20different%20today.%20The%20structure%20of%20the%20state%20is%20apparently%20the%20same%3B%20but%20it%20is%20being%20hollowed%20out.%20There%20is%20an%20organised%20force%20that%20has%20risen%20to%20complement%20state%20power.%20This%20organised%20force%20takes%20on%20any%20resistance%20that%20comes%20from%20the%20people%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20compact%20between%20the%20state%20and%20this%20kind%20of%20intimidation%20politics.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20these%20forces%20do%20not%20comprise%20fringe%20elements%3B%20they%20are%20a%20significant%20political%20force%20in%20the%20country%2C%20they%20are%20%E2%80%98mainstream%E2%80%99.%20They%20help%20to%20build%20a%20kind%20of%20destructive%20and%20sectarian%20politics.%20The%20object%20is%20to%20exclude%20people%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20their%20community%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20eroding%20the%20citizenship%20rights%20of%20some%20Indians.%20The%20Congress%20did%20not%20have%20all%20these%20exclusionary%20politics%20in%20its%20genetic%20composition%3B%20the%20RSS%20has%20them%20in%20its%20genes.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20crucial%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20difference%20between%20then%20and%20now%20is%20the%20sustained%20and%20multifarious%20attacks%20we%20see%20today%20on%20our%20secular%20ethos%2C%20on%20culture%2C%20on%20education%2C%20science%20and%20reason.%20This%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20part%20of%20the%20ideology-driven%20project%20of%20building%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20which%20will%20have%20little%20to%20do%20with%20the%20inclusive%2C%20secular%20nation%20with%20a%20scientific%20outlook%20envisioned%20by%20so%20many%20of%20our%20freedom%20fighters.%20The%20Hindutva%20brigade%20failed%20the%20national%20movement.%20They%20did%20not%20fight%20for%20independence.%20So%20their%20vision%20for%20India%20is%20to%20take%20it%20onto%20a%20different%20trajectory%20from%20the%20attempt%20in%201947%20which%20had%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20consensus%20among%20the%20people.%20Their%20battle%20was%20and%20has%20been%20against%20the%20Muslims.%20To%20put%20it%20another%20way%2C%20possibly%20a%20more%20precise%20way%2C%20it%20was%2C%20and%20is%2C%20for%20Hindu%20supremacy.%20The%20India%20they%20are%20fighting%20for%20will%20have%20one%20religion%20and%20one%20people%2C%20Hindi-Hindu-%20Hindu%20Rashtra%3B%20this%20means%20large%20numbers%20of%20Indians%20will%20become%20second-class%20citizens.%20In%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20Hindu%20supremacists%20are%20still%20fighting%20their%20battle%20in%20the%20past%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20by%20renaming%20streets%20and%20cities%2C%20pulling%20down%20monuments%2C%20or%20finding%20mandirs%20everywhere.%20The%20battle%20they%20are%20engaged%20in%20looks%20backwards%3B%20they%20have%20nothing%20to%20offer%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi-1024x512.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F14183024%2FNarendra-Modi-Indira-Gandhi-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-279448%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENarendra%20Modi%20and%20Indira-Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20we%20resist%20this%20new%20powerful%20Emergency%20without%20a%20name%3F%20I%20think%20we%20need%20a%20much%20larger%20coming%20together%20of%20people.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement%20has%20been%20so%20important.%20In%20Western%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Muslim%20and%20Jat%20farmers%20came%20together%20through%20the%20movement.%20To%20understand%20how%20significant%20this%20is%2C%20we%20have%20to%20recall%20that%20in%20September%202013%2C%20riots%20broke%20out%20between%20Muslims%20and%20Jats%20in%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20district.%20Several%20members%20of%20the%20BJP%20were%20accused%20of%20instigating%20the%20riots%3B%20and%20the%20BJP%20won%20the%20subsequent%20general%20and%20assembly%20elections%20from%20the%20region.%20The%20fracturing%20between%20the%20two%20communities%20that%20took%20place%20during%20the%20Muzaffarnagar%20riots%20was%2C%20to%20some%20extent%2C%20healed%20by%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMovements%20build%20this%20kind%20of%20unity.%20This%20is%20why%20the%20rightwing%20considers%20movements%20based%20on%20class%20issues%20dangerous%3A%20they%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20build%20on%20caste%20and%20community%20divisions%2C%20which%20is%20what%20the%20BJP%20does.%20Is%20it%20any%20surprise%20that%20movements%20%E2%80%94%20from%20farmers%E2%80%99%20movements%20and%20workers%E2%80%99%20movements%20to%20anti-caste%20movements%20and%20students%E2%80%99%20movements%20%E2%80%94%20become%20ideological%20threats%20to%20the%20RSS%20and%20the%20BJP%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Congress%20Emergency%2C%20the%20jailers%20were%20quite%20aware%20that%20some%20of%20the%20people%20they%20were%20holding%20in%20prison%20could%20well%20become%20the%20rulers%20someday.%20That%20was%20a%20clear%20motive%20to%20treat%20these%20prisoners%20differently.%20Mrs%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20government%20also%20accepted%20the%20fact%20that%20these%20prisoners%20were%20not%20%E2%80%98ordinary%E2%80%99%20people%20they%20had%20to%20%E2%80%98break%E2%80%99.%20Their%20plan%20of%20action%20was%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20media%20and%20its%20messaging%2C%20and%20to%20marginalise%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20methods%2C%20and%20in%20fact%20the%20overall%20plan%20to%20silence%20people%2C%20seems%20quite%20different%20today.%20The%20driving%20question%20seems%20to%20be%20How%20do%20we%20break%20the%20people%20who%20are%20standing%20up%20to%20us%3F%20The%20aim%20is%20to%20remould%20the%20state%20without%20these%20dissident%20voices%3B%20and%20ensure%20that%20nobody%20is%20able%20to%20stand%20up%20to%20the%20government%20or%20the%20right-wing%20forces%20in%20all%20their%20various%20avatars.%20This%20may%20explain%20some%20of%20the%20terrible%20pettiness%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20the%20current%20regime%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20political%20prisoners.%20The%20most%20obvious%20example%20is%20that%20of%20Stan%20Swamy%2C%20the%2083-year-old%20activist%20who%20worked%20with%20Adivasis%20and%20who%20was%20jailed%20for%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20the%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20case.%20Here%20was%20a%20frail%20old%20man%20who%20suffered%20from%20various%20medical%20conditions%20including%20Parkinson%E2%80%99s.%20He%20had%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20sipper%20and%20straw%20because%20of%20the%20tremors%20in%20his%20hands.%20The%20NIA%20%E2%80%98sought%20time%E2%80%99%20to%20consider%20his%20request%3B%20a%20special%20court%20turned%20down%20the%20request.%20The%20activist%20had%20to%20make%20a%20fresh%20application%20for%20the%20sipper%20cup%20as%20well%20as%20winter%20clothes.%20Such%20banal%20acts%20of%20cruelty%2C%20such%20dehumanising%20acts%2C%20seem%20to%20carry%20a%20message%3A%20We%20can%20do%20anything%20we%20want%20to%20you%2C%20and%20no%20one%20can%20stop%20us.%20As%20long%20as%20the%20courts%20do%20not%20give%20political%20prisoners%20the%20protection%20they%20should%2C%20the%20message%20may%20well%20continue%20to%20hold%20true.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOur%20hope%20is%20that%20as%20these%20flagrant%20violations%20of%20rights%20become%20more%20visible%2C%20more%20questions%20will%20also%20grow%20audible.%20One%20positive%20development%20is%20that%20the%20courts%20seem%20to%20be%20taking%20up%20more%20of%20these%20cases.%20Perhaps%20the%20ice%20is%20cracking%20a%20little%3F%20We%20will%20have%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Chr%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20excerpt%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3EKeeping%20Up%20the%20Good%20Fight%3Cem%3E%20is%20republished%20with%20permission%20from%20LeftWord%20Books.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699257054000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06131557%2FScreenshot-2023-11-06-at-1.15.11%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fdifference-then-and-now-prabir-purkayastha-book-excerpt%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ideologically%2C%20the%20Congress%20was%20not%20following%20the%20Savarkar%20thesis%20which%20plays%20out%20today%20both%20formally%20and%20informally%3A%20Minorities%20can%20remain%20in%20the%20country%20but%20only%20as%20second-class%20citizens.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fdifference-then-and-now-prabir-purkayastha-book-excerpt%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Chaupal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06121548%2FScreenshot-2023-11-06-at-12.15.2.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBeyond%20politics%2C%20the%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20is%20a%20revolutionary%20document.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20public%20document%2C%20the%20first%20ever%20after%201931%2C%20allowing%20for%20people%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20be%20counted.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWe%20go%20down%20to%20the%20wire%2C%20on%20what%20each%20of%20the%20numbers%20unveiled%20mean.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWho%20are%20the%20people%20referred%20to%20by%20percentages%20in%20the%20survey%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EToday%20we%20look%20at%20Chaupal%20(748%2C059%20people)%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20concept%20of%20a%20caste-based%20society%20has%20led%20to%20two%20sharply%20divided%20sections%20within%20it%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20them%20does%20labour%2C%20while%20the%20other%20consumes%20the%20goods%20produced%20through%20that%20labour.%20This%20labour%E2%80%99s%20products%20are%20not%20always%20visible%20in%20the%20physical%20form.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20when%20a%20barber%20works%2C%20his%20labour%20is%20clearly%20visible.%20The%20beauty%20of%20a%20person%20is%20enhanced%20when%20he%20gets%20shaved%20by%20him.%20His%20fingernails%20are%20no%20longer%20dirty%20after%20being%20clipped.%20If%20a%20potter%20makes%20a%20pot%2C%20the%20utensil%20is%20the%20proof%20of%20his%20labour.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20how%20will%20the%20labour%20of%20those%20who%20carry%20someone%E2%80%99s%20palanquin%20be%20seen%3F%20If%20someone%20stands%20guard%20at%20someone%E2%80%99s%20door%20with%20a%20stick%2C%20is%20his%20labour%20tangible%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20346px)%2085vw%2C%20346px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22346%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742.jpg%20838w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-210x300.jpg%20210w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30093107%2FIMG_2742-715x1024.jpg%20715w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682410%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22495%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20form%20of%20labour%20is%20called%20a%20service%20and%20according%20to%20modern%20economics%2C%20it%20is%20part%20of%20the%20service%20sector.%20But%20modern%20concepts%20do%20not%20work%20in%20the%20case%20of%20castes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20a%20caste%20group%20in%20Bihar%20called%20Chaupal.%20The%20literal%20meaning%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echaupal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20someone%20who%20sustains%20in%20all%20four%20directions%20or%20ways.%20It%20actually%20means%20someone%20who%20toils%20in%20the%20field%20and%20does%20farming%2C%20is%20a%20craftsman%2C%20is%20a%20protector%20and%20a%20cleaner%20or%20sweeper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20caste-based%20system%20and%20the%20concept%20of%20patriarchy%20largely%20hinge%20on%20making%20one%20serve%20and%20in%20this%20assumption%20of%20subservience%20and%20service%2C%20Chaupals%20are%20no%20exception.%20Communities%20doing%20labour%20are%20made%20into%20servants.%20This%20means%20that%20if%20someone%20belongs%20to%20an%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%2C%20their%20job%20is%20to%20rule%2C%20thanks%20largely%20to%20his%20access%20to%20resources.%20Governance%20does%20not%20mean%20being%20elected%20as%20an%20MP%20or%20an%20MLA.%20It%20also%20means%20the%20ability%20to%20lead%20a%20quality%20life%20without%20bearing%20any%20hardships.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20scene%20commonly%20witnessed%20in%20villages%20even%20today.%20The%20Brahmin%20priest%20can%20roam%20around%20the%20area%20with%20a%20plate%20in%20his%20hand%20and%20yet%20have%20more%20than%20two%20meals%20a%20day.%20But%20people%20of%20other%20castes%20cannot%20do%20so.%20One%2C%20the%20society%20will%20not%20give%20them%20anything%20but%20will%20only%20hurl%20abuses.%20Second%2C%20the%20labour%20castes%20are%20not%20used%20to%20this%20either.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20people%20of%20Chaupal%20caste%20are%20not%20assigned%20any%20definite%20ancestral%20line%20of%20work.%20They%20have%20been%20doing%20all%20kinds%20of%20labour.%20However%2C%20seldom%20did%20they%20get%20the%20wages%20and%20social%20rights%20that%20they%20have%20deserved.%20The%20concept%20of%20hierarchy%20in%20the%20caste%20system%20meant%20that%20for%20the%20people%20of%20castes%20like%20Kevat%2C%20Mallah%2C%20Nishad%2C%20Bind%2C%20Beldar%20and%20Noniya%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Chaupals%20who%20were%20meant%20to%20be%20the%20traditional%20labourers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20means%20that%20even%20though%20there%20was%20equality%20among%20many%20caste%20groups%20in%20terms%20of%20work%2C%20not%20everyone%20was%20equal%20at%20the%20social%20level.%20They%20are%20not%20equal%20even%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20now%20that%20we%20have%20a%20democracy%2C%20circumstances%20have%20changed%20a%20little.%20Those%20caste%20groups%20which%20were%20earlier%20considered%20ignoble%20now%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20elections.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20reason%20why%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20seems%20to%20have%20Hinduised%20the%20Chaupal%20caste.%20In%20fact%2C%20they%20have%20been%20doing%20it%20not%20only%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Chaupals%2C%20but%20with%20all%20the%20labour%20castes.%20For%20example%2C%20they%20used%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERamayana%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20describe%20Kevat%20and%20Mallah%20castes%20as%20the%20followers%20of%20Hindu%20religion.%20The%20RSS%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20led%20an%20innovative%20experiment%20to%20Brahminise%20the%20Chaupal%20caste.%20Kameshwar%20Chaupal%2C%20a%20person%20from%20the%20caste%20which%20is%20categorised%20as%20a%20Scheduled%20Caste%20in%20Bihar%2C%20was%20roped%20in%20to%20lay%20the%20first%20brick%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20may%20ask%20how%20the%20Chaupal%20caste%20came%20to%20be%20included%20in%20the%20category%20of%20Scheduled%20Castes%2C%20even%20though%20this%20caste%20has%20never%20been%20%E2%80%98untouchable%E2%80%99%20for%20Brahmins.%20Another%20such%20tribe%20is%20Tharu%2C%20which%20has%20a%20population%20of%201%2C92%2C050%20in%20Bihar.%20The%20people%20of%20the%20tribe%20are%20now%20being%20convinced%20that%20they%20have%20traditionally%20been%20equivalent%20to%20the%20Rajput%20caste.%20The%20traditions%20of%20the%20Tharu%20community%20have%20also%20been%20a%20factor%20behind%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20people%20of%20Chaupal%20caste%20never%20called%20themselves%20descendants%20of%20Rajputs%20or%20Brahmins.%20Moreover%2C%20had%20they%20been%20the%20descendants%20of%20Rajput%20or%20Brahmin%20castes%2C%20why%20would%20they%20carry%20palanquins%2C%20stand%20guard%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20doors%2C%20or%20do%20forced%20labour%20in%20the%20fields%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20Hinduisation%20of%20Chaupal%20caste%20and%2C%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20its%20transformation%20from%20non-Dalit%20to%20Dalit%20has%20been%20done%20not%20without%20reason.%20According%20to%20the%20Caste-Based%20Census%20Report%202022%2C%20the%20population%20of%20this%20caste%20in%20Bihar%20is%20748%2C059.%20Interestingly%2C%20this%20population%20is%20spread%20over%20parts%20of%20north%20and%20east%20Bihar.%20Thus%2C%20the%20arithmetic%20is%20as%20much%20sociological%20as%20it%20is%20political.%20For%20example%2C%20among%20the%20Dalit%20castes%20of%20Bihar%2C%20the%20Dhobi%20caste%20is%20undoubtedly%20present%20in%20the%20entire%20state%2C%20but%20the%20population%20is%201%2C096%2C158%20whereas%20the%20Nutt%20caste%2C%20which%20is%20a%20Scheduled%20Caste%2C%20has%20a%20population%20of%20105%2C063.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20are%20the%20figures%20which%20indicate%20why%20the%20Chaupals%2C%20who%20were%20earlier%20not%20considered%20Dalits%20because%20they%20were%20not%20%E2%80%98untouchable%E2%80%99%2C%20were%20categorised%20as%20Dalits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%20categorising%20the%20people%20of%20this%20caste%20as%20Dalits%2C%20the%20caste%20equation%20has%20been%20changed%20in%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20assembly%20constituencies%20in%20Bihar%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20no%20candidate%20can%20win%20without%20their%20votes.%20No%20matter%20which%20party%20it%20is%2C%20they%20have%20to%20look%20after%20the%20interests%20of%20this%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20no%20official%20history%20of%20the%20Chaupal%20caste%20and%20its%20people.%20History%2C%20anyway%2C%20belongs%20to%20the%20ruling%20classes.%20The%20subjects%20are%20only%20sporadically%20mentioned%20in%20historical%20accounts.%20British%20ethnologist%20Robert%20Wayne%20Russell%20has%20described%20the%20Chaupal%20as%20a%20large%20non-Aryan%20caste%20of%20Bihar%20and%20the%20United%20Provinces%20(present-day%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Uttarakhand).%20Regarding%20their%20activities%2C%20another%20British%20ethnographer%2C%20Sir%20Herbert%20Hope%20Risley%2C%20wrote%20that%20apart%20from%20farming%2C%20they%20were%20involved%20in%20soil%20cutting%2C%20fishing%2C%20hunting%20and%20collecting%20indigenous%20herbs%20and%20medicines%20for%20a%20livelihood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Chaupal%20caste%20has%20now%20transformed%20into%20a%20political%20caste%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20political%20scheme.%20The%20RSS%20has%20also%20installed%20Hindu%20deities%20in%20their%20settlements%2C%20leading%20to%20Chaupal%20caste%20members%20getting%20rid%20of%20their%20family%20deities%20and%20perpetuating%20a%20cycle%20of%20subservience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20Hindi%20by%20Naushin%20Rehman.%20Read%20the%20Hindi%20original%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F260208%2Fbihar-caste-survey-what-is-the-history-of-chaupal-caste%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERead%20earlier%20parts%20of%20the%20series%20on%20the%20following%20communities%20by%20clicking%20on%20their%20names%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-ghasi%5C%22%3EGhasi%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3ESantrash%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-santrash%5C%22%3EMadaria%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-koeri-kushwaha%5C%22%3EKoeri%2FKushwaha%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20series%20is%20available%20in%20Hindi%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewirehindi.com%2F260200%2Fbihar-caste-survey-who-are-the-santarash%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20in%20Urdu%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewireurdu.com%2Fauthor%2Fnaval-kishor-kumar%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699256763000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F06121548%2FScreenshot-2023-11-06-at-12.15.2.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20figures%20indicate%20the%20electoral%20compulsions%20that%20have%20led%20to%20the%20Chaupals%2C%20who%20were%20earlier%20not%20considered%20Dalits%20because%20they%20were%20not%20%E2%80%98untouchable%E2%80%99%2C%20being%20now%20considered%20so.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-chaupal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22School%20caretaker%20'contaminated%20food%20with%20bodily%20fluids%20and%20wiped%20private%20parts%20on%20kitchen%20utensils'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699255920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F70x70%2Fskynews-giovanni-impellizzeri_6350146.png%3F20231106082505%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnew-jersey-school-caretaker-arrested-after-food-contaminated-with-bodily-fluids-and-offered-to-students-13001777%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20school%20caretaker%20in%20the%20US%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20contaminating%20food%20and%20kitchen%20utensils%20with%20bodily%20fluids%20and%20bleach.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fnew-jersey-school-caretaker-arrested-after-food-contaminated-with-bodily-fluids-and-offered-to-students-13001777%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnew-jersey-school-caretaker-arrested-after-food-contaminated-with-bodily-fluids-and-offered-to-students-13001777%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fnew-jersey-school-caretaker-arrested-after-food-contaminated-with-bodily-fluids-and-offered-to-students-13001777%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trend%20of%20Governors%20Acting%20on%20Bills%20Only%20After%20State%20Governments%20Approach%20Courts%20Must%20Stop%3A%20SC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F21013004%2FIMG_3491.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Monday%2C%20November%206%2C%20expressed%20anguish%20that%20state%20governments%20have%20to%20approach%20the%20courts%20to%20get%20governors%20to%20act%20on%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20legislature.%20The%20top%20court%20made%20this%20oral%20observation%20while%20hearing%20a%20writ%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20Punjab%20government%20challenging%20the%20inaction%20of%20governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit%20on%20seven%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fwhy-governors-act-on-bills-only-after-state-govts-approach-courts-this-has-to-stop-supreme-court-241676%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20orally%20said%20that%20the%20trend%20of%20governors%20acting%20on%20Bills%20only%20after%20the%20government%20approaches%20the%20court%20must%20stop%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20in%20response%20to%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20informing%20the%20bench%20that%20governor%20Purohit%20took%20%E2%80%9Cappropriate%20decisions%E2%80%9D%20on%20some%20Bills%20and%20would%20convey%20the%20details%20by%20Friday%20(November%2010).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20does%20the%20party%20have%20to%20come%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3F%20Governors%20act%20only%20when%20matters%20reach%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20This%20has%20to%20stop.%20You%20come%20to%20Supreme%20Court%20then%20the%20Governor%20starts%20acting.%20This%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20similar%20situation%20had%20occurred%20in%20the%20past%20in%20Telangana%2C%20when%20the%20governor%20acted%20on%20the%20pending%20Bills%20only%20after%20the%20government%20filed%20a%20writ%20petition%20in%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGovernors%20should%20not%20be%20oblivious%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20are%20not%20elected%20authorities%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Punjab%20government%2C%20said%20Bills%20that%20the%20governor%20did%20not%20act%20on%20included%20those%20on%20fiscal%20management%20and%20amendments%20to%20GST%2C%20affecting%20governance.%20To%20this%2C%20the%20CJI%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CLittle%20bit%20of%20soul%20searching%20needed%20from%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20Governor.%20Governor%20must%20know%20that%20he%20is%20not%20an%20elected%20representative%E2%80%A6%20He%20can%20withhold%20assent%20and%20send%20it%20back%20once..%20This%20is%20particularly%20on%20money%20bills%20%E2%80%A6%20Why%20should%20parties%20be%20required%20to%20move%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20convening%20the%20House%3F%20%E2%80%A6%20We%20are%20the%20oldest%20democracy%20and%20these%20issues%20must%20be%20sorted%20between%20the%20Chief%20Minister%20and%20the%20Governor.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20also%20comprising%20Justices%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20agreed%20to%20hear%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fkerala-moves-sc-governor-arif-mohammad-khan-bills-hold-indefinitely%5C%22%3Esimilar%20petitions%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20by%20the%20Kerala%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20governments%20also%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699254929000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F21013004%2FIMG_3491.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-inaction-bills-supreme-court-punjab%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CJI%20Chandrachud%20made%20this%20oral%20observation%20while%20hearing%20a%20writ%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20Punjab%20government%20challenging%20the%20inaction%20of%20governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit%20on%20seven%20Bills.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovernors-inaction-bills-supreme-court-punjab%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20sacks%20employee%20over%20antisemitic%20Instagram%20message%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699254832000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105003917%2Cimgsize-32338.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisrael-hamas-war-who-is-natasha-dach-and-why-apple-fired-her%2Farticleshow%2F105003865.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Natasha%20Dach's%20post%20was%20widely%20condemned%20by%20social%20media%20users%2C%20who%20tagged%20Apple%20and%20its%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%2C%20and%20demanded%20action%20against%20her.%20Some%20also%20questioned%20her%20loyalty%20to%20the%20US%20and%20her%20sympathy%20for%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20militant%20group%20that%20is%20designated%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organization%20by%20the%20US%20and%20many%20other%20countries.%20Dach%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20technical%20specialist%20and%20manager%20apprentice%20at%20Apple%2C%20deleted%20her%20Instagram%20and%20LinkedIn%20accounts%20after%20receiving%20backlash%20for%20her%20remarks.%20She%20was%20also%20removed%20from%20Apple's%20official%20employee%20directory.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22State-Sponsored%20Cyber%20Attacks%20Against%20India%20Went%20Up%20by%20278%25%20Between%202021%20and%20September%202023%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03144731%2Fimage-1469.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EState-sponsored%20cyber%20attacks%20against%20India%20increased%20by%20278%25%20between%202021%20and%20September%202023%2C%20with%20services%20companies%2C%20including%20information%20technology%20(IT)%20and%20business%20process%20outsourcing%20(BPO)%20firms%2C%20seeing%20the%20highest%20share%20of%20attacks%2C%20a%20new%20report%20has%20found.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20period%2C%20targeted%20cyber%20attacks%20on%20government%20agencies%20went%20up%20by%20460%25%2C%20while%20startups%20and%20small%20and%20medium%20enterprises%20(SMEs)%20saw%20a%20whopping%20increase%20by%20508%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%202023%20India%20Threat%20Landscape%20Report%20by%20Singapore-based%20cybersecurity%20firm%20Cyfirma%2C%20India%20is%20the%20most%20targeted%20country%20globally%2C%20facing%2013.7%25%20of%20all%20cyber%20attacks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Ftech%2Ftechnology%2Findia-most-targeted-country-by-cyber-attackers-report%2Farticleshow%2F104989856.cms%23%3A~%3Atext%3DState%252Dsponsored%2520cyber%2520attacks%2520against%2Cthe%2520highest%2520share%2520of%2520attacks.%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20the%20second%20most%20targeted%20country%2C%20with%209.6%25%20of%20all%20attacks.%20Indonesia%20and%20China%20follow%2C%20with%209.3%25%20and%204.5%25%20of%20all%20attacks%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECyfirma%20founder%20and%20chief%20executive%20Kumar%20Ritesh%20told%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20India%20is%20also%20experiencing%20a%20higher%20proportion%20of%20foreign%20state-influenced%20cyber%20attacks%20compared%20to%20the%20global%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20globally%2C%20almost%2068%25%20of%20cyber%20attacks%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%20were%20state-sponsored.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20India%20number%2C%20this%20is%20slightly%20higher%2C%20at%2072%25%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECyfirma%20found%20that%20services%20companies%2C%20including%20IT%20and%20BPO%2C%20were%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%2014.3%25%20of%20cyber%20attacks%20between%20March%202021%20and%20September%202023.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20manufacturing%20at%2011.6%25%2C%20and%20healthcare%20and%20education%20at%20around%2010%25%20each.%20Retail%2C%20including%20online%20platforms%2C%20saw%209.8%25%20of%20attacks%20while%20government%20agencies%20saw%209.6%25.%20Banking%20and%20financial%20services%20institutions%2C%20automobiles%2C%20and%20airlines%20saw%209.5%25%2C%208.3%25%2C%20and%206.1%25%20of%20attacks%2C%20respectively%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202015-16%2C%2058-59%25%20of%20cyber%20attacks%20on%20India%20were%20from%20Pakistani%20threat%20actors%20or%20operators%20from%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20he%20told%20the%20newspaper.%20Today%2C%20only%206.4%25%20of%20threats%20are%20from%20Pakistani%20actors%20or%20their%20affiliates%2C%20while%2079%25%20are%20from%20China%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20India%20needs%20a%20better%20enforcement%20of%20cybersecurity%20policies%20and%20greater%20awareness%2C%20especially%20among%20SMEs%20and%20startups%2C%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20sophisticated%20cybercriminals%20they%20are%20up%20against%2C%20Ritesh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20as%20brand%20India%20are%20elevating%20ourselves%2C%20but%20it%20looks%20like%20cybercriminals%20are%20also%20elevating%20themselves%20because%20they%20know%20that%20we%20are%20becoming%20quite%20an%20influential%20force%20in%20the%20world%20ecosystem%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ritesh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fnearly-60-of-healthcare-organisations-in-india-hit-by-cyberattacks-in-past-year-report%5C%22%3ENearly%2060%25%20Of%20Healthcare%20Organisations%20in%20India%20Hit%20by%20Cyberattacks%20in%20Past%20Year%3A%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20cybersecurity%20weakness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20digitisation%20has%20accelerated%20the%20need%20for%20cybersecurity%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20cybersecurity%20regulations%20are%20weak%20and%20inadequate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20on%20November%2030%2C%20the%20website%20of%20the%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Medical%20Research%20(ICMR)%20faced%20around%206%2C000%20hacking%20attempts%20in%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20happened%20a%20week%20after%20five%20servers%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Faiims-servers-cyberattack-ransomware-rajya-sabha%5C%22%3Ehad%20been%20hacked%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20ransomware.%20An%20estimated%201.3%20terabytes%20of%20data%20was%20encrypted.%20The%20hackers%20had%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20AIIMS%20to%20access%20its%20own%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2031%2C%202023%2C%20in%20a%20massive%20data%20breach%2C%20information%20of%20over%2081.5%20crore%20Indians%20with%20the%20ICMR%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Fhealthcare%2Fnews-healthcare%2Fquestions-abound-but-icmr-still-silent-on-the-data-leak%2F3293107%2F%5C%22%3Ewere%20sold%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20dark%20web.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%20Technology%20Review%20CyberDefense%20Index%20(CDI)%202022%2F23%20ranked%20India%20at%20No.%2017%20out%20of%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMIT%E2%80%99s%20CDI%20is%20the%20%E2%80%98first-of-its-kind%E2%80%99%20annual%20comparative%20ranking%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%2020%20largest%20and%20most%20digital%20economies%20on%20their%20preparation%20against%2C%20and%20response%20and%20recovery%20from%2C%20cybersecurity%20threats%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcio.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fdigital-security%2Fcybersecurity-how-does-india-perform-at-the-global-stage%2F99628852%5C%22%3E%20another%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20struggles%2C%20despite%20a%20digitally%20forward%20government%20and%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20IT-enabled%20service%20sectors.%20This%20powerful%20tech%20force%20lacks%20critical%20infrastructure%2C%20has%20poor%20national%20digital%20economy%20adoption%2C%20and%20weak%20cybersecurity%20regulation.%20Despite%20cyberattacks%20and%20calls%20for%20cybersecurity%20laws%20and%20a%20dedicated%20ministry%2C%20India%20has%20opted%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EET%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20report%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20increasing%20number%20of%20cyberattacks%20has%20called%20for%20a%20cybersecurity%20law%20and%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20dedicated%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExperts%20have%20also%20pointed%20to%20the%20need%20for%20job%20creation%20in%20the%20cybersecurity%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20the%20second%20highest%20number%20of%20active%20internet%20users%20after%20China%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Findia-suffering-high-cybersecurity-skill-gap-40k-open-positions-report-123062100397_1.html%5C%22%3Erepresents%3C%2Fa%3E%20only%206%25%20of%20the%20global%20cybersecurity%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERajeev%20Sharma%2C%20CEO%20and%20CIO%2C%20Sysquark%20Technologies%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%20an%20IT%20services%20company%20told%20the%20newspaper%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20would%20worry%20about%20theft%20when%20you%20have%20something%20to%20protect.%20Now%20think%20as%20a%20country%20instead%20of%20as%20a%20company.%20Companies%20will%20always%20have%20data%20to%20protect%20but%20they%20will%20always%20be%20short%20of%20resources.%20For%20a%20resource%2C%20security%20comes%20last%20in%20mind%20because%20he%20is%20busy%20doing%20firefighting.%20For%20a%20company%2C%20hiring%20more%20resources%20is%20not%20cost-effective%20since%20only%20a%20handful%20of%20customers%20are%20planning%20to%20buy%20the%20services%2Fgoods%20you%20are%20manufacturing.%20To%20strengthen%20the%20buying%20power%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20the%20cost-effectiveness%20of%20the%20resources%2C%20the%20first%20need%20is%20to%20create%20jobs.%20And%20I%20am%20purely%20talking%20from%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20standpoint.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20standpoint%2C%20if%20we%20have%20a%20bigger%20coffer%2C%20we%20will%20be%20more%20interested%20in%20hiring%20resources%20who%20are%20specialised%20in%20the%20desired%20jobs.%20Cross-skilling%20is%20only%20a%20compromise%20on%20expertise.%20From%20a%20resource%20standpoint%2C%20since%20I%20have%20more%20time%2C%20I%20might%20like%20to%20learn%20new%20skills%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMoneycontrol%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneycontrol.com%2Fnews%2Fopinion%2Fdigital-india-act-heres-how-it-should-fix-indias-cybersecurity-weaknesses-11038701.html%5C%22%3Ehas%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20India%20could%20fix%20its%20cybersecurity%20weakness.%20It%20said%20that%20the%20upcoming%20Digital%20India%20Act%20offers%20an%20opportunity%20to%20streamline%20and%20modernise%20India%E2%80%99s%20cybersecurity%20framework%2C%20addressing%20the%20existing%20gaps%20and%20inefficiencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699253135000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03144731%2Fimage-1469.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fstate-sponsored-cyber-attacks-against-india-went-up-by-278-between-2021-and-september-2023-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20the%202023%20India%20Threat%20Landscape%20Report%20by%20Singapore-based%20cybersecurity%20firm%20Cyfirma%2C%20India%20is%20the%20most%20targeted%20country%20globally%2C%20facing%2013.7%25%20of%20all%20cyber%20attacks.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fstate-sponsored-cyber-attacks-against-india-went-up-by-278-between-2021-and-september-2023-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Prince%20William%20goes%20dragon%20boating%20in%20Si